SarPplot 
System Statics Ploter 

its simple application which takes output of atsar application and put it 
into Gnuplot config files , kind of useful on server boxes for performance
analyze .

the output is Png , and SarPplot provide analyze for :

cpu (Separated for cpu + total )
process load
disk (plot per disk)
disk-partition (plot per partition)
memory & swap
paging & swapping
interrupts
kernel-resources
tty activity
net-interf (general) (plot for each nic)
net-interf (errors) (plot for each nic)
ip   v4    (general)
ip   v4    (errors)
tcp  v4    (general)
tcp  v4    (errors)
udp  v4
icmp v4    (general)
icmp v4    (per type)
nfs        (general)
nfs        (errors)
nfs        (server)
nfs-rpc    (%calls)


syntax is Simple :
./sarpplot <interval> <sample number>

Example :
./sarpplot 1 10
takes 10 sample each second .


